snippet.textDisplay:
Let's take a moment to appreciate that it usually takes well over a month for a TechLinked video to breach 800k
And this will be a million in like THREE DAYS since posting
EDIT: You know what, let me make another call: #1 Techlinked video by two weeks since publishing
EDIT2: I believe in our girl(I'm checking this more often than fucking miners do the rate of bitcoin), but it seems I put a rather conservative upper bound there(forgive me, I've been reading a lot on managing floating point error recently). As of now(1:50am gmt+3) it's at 1.129m views, making it #7 top video on the channel, within spitting distance(5 and 17k, PFFT) of #5(1.146) and #6(1,134). Got a bit more than half a mil views to go, I expect it to kind of lose steam exponentially, hence the two weeks, we'll see. Won't be readjusting my estimate, it's not a fair game that way :)
EDDI3: 3.3.21, 4:57am gmt+3 - #5, 1,214m views
EDI4H: 4.3.21, #4
PIA5: as of 5.3.21, it's 40k before #3(shown at #5 atm)
Edit 6, final: 11.3, two weeks since posting, 1.345M, #3. Damn solid result if not the #1 I wanted :D
